# Java Fundamentals
Java Switch Statements:
--Switch statements are used to avoid nested if else;
--Switch Statement is executes the case which matches the expression
--there is break and default keywords in switch statement
--break is used to breaks out from the switch statements
--defualt is used for executes the default statements if there is no match found to expression
--if expression matched to one of the case then it will executes the block of code of that case and breaks the execution of switch statements
--if break is not given then all of the cases are executes after matched expression until the break.
